A yearly subscription is refundable within 14 days of purchase and includes a 365-day membership. Rothschild & Co is an adviser on the deal, the people said. Coca-Cola Beverages South Africa said it will comment at a media briefing later Friday. Coca-Cola in the US didn’t immediately respond to a request for comment outside normal business hours. The broader Coca-Cola Beverages Africa is based in the coastal town of Port Elizabeth and serves 12 countries, including Kenya, Ethiopia and Ghana, according to the website. It accounts for about 40% of the Atlanta-based company’s drinks sold on the continent. The value of the entire business is about R45 billion, the people said, meaning the new investors are getting a discounted price. The deal will help benefit employees and other partners as well as non-White investors, they said, though the exact structure is as yet unclear.